and sledging. Itâs accessible mainly during the summer months due to heavy snowfall in winter.

3. **Hadimba Temple**: Also known as Dhungri Temple

a character from the Indian epic Mahabharata. Surrounded by cedar forests

it is known for its unique architecture and serene ambiance.

4. **Manu Temple**: Situated in Old Manali
this temple is dedicated to the sage Manu

believed to be the creator of the world and the writer of Manusmriti. The temple is set in a picturesque location with views of the surrounding hills and valleys.

5. **Vashisht Hot Springs**: Located in the village of Vashisht
these natural hot springs are believed to have medicinal properties. The village is also known for its beautiful Vashisht Temple

and offers an opportunity for relaxation in the warm waters amidst a serene setting.

6. **Old Manali**: This charming part of Manali is known for its laid-back vibe
and quaint cafes. Itâs a great place to explore traditional Himachali culture

and enjoy the scenic beauty of the region with views of the Beas River and surrounding mountains.
